main event: A civilian observer in Anchorage, Kentucky spotted a single unidentified aerial object on March 23, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for 2 hours and 30 seconds.
The object appeared silvery with a greenish hue and was brighter than the brightest stars.
The object exhibited various behaviors like appearing to stand still, suddenly speeding up or slowing down, and flashing or flickering.
The observer was widely read about UFOs and had some knowledge of astronomy.
The observer reported the sighting to the Air Force shortly after it occurred.
